    "comment": "Rationale: Overexpressed GFP-tagged msec7-1 is localized to presynaptic regions in Xenopus neuromuscular junctions (Fig. 2). Overexpression of msec7-1 causes a translocation of ARF6 from endosomal compartments to the plasma membrane in HEK293 cells (Fig. 1). mSec7-1 contains a pleckstrin-homology domain, which mediates an enhancement of the GEF activity by its binding to PIP2.. Experimental description: - Fig.1 Expression vectors for full length rat msec7-1 were generated...\n- Fig. 2 Synaptic localization shown with Xenopus cell culture that overexpresses rat mSec.",
